<title>GERMANY: Schering gets cartel approval for Leiras takeover.</title>
<headline>Schering gets cartel approval for Leiras takeover.</headline>
<dateline>BERLIN 1996-09-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>German drugs group Schering AG said on Monday it had received cartel office approval to complete an earlier announced takeover of Finnish confectionery and packaging group Huhtamaki Oy's Leiras unit.</p>
<p>Schering, the world's largest manufacturer of oral contraceptives, said it would buy the Finnish group in July but said the deal still depended on cartel office approval.</p>
<p>With Leiras, strong in hormonal contraceptives and osteoporosis drugs, Schering hopes to post &quot;overproportional&quot; growth in the pharmaceuticals sector.</p>
<p>The deal was valued around 1.43 billion markka ($319 million).</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525 ($ = 4.478 Finnish Markka)</p>
